text: Rostam County () is a county in Fars Province in Iran. The capital of the county is Masiri.Gitashenasi Province Atlas of Iranاطلس گیتاشناسی استان‌های ایران At the 2006 census, the county's population was 45,377, in 9,134 families. The county is subdivided into two districts: the Central District and Sorna District. The county has two cities: Masiri and Kupon. == References == Category:Counties in Fars Province
